TITLE: Lebanon investigates shooting outside US embassy
SUMMARY: An unknown gunman has opened fire outside Lebanon’s U.S. Embassy northeast of the capital of Beirut. Authorities have launched an investigation into the shooting.

TITLE: Israeli authorities find stolen military tank in junkyard
SUMMARY: Authorities in Israel have arrested two suspects tied to the theft of an unarmed military tank which was found in a junkyard Wednesday.

TITLE: Singapore police investigating money laundering scheme uncover more gold bars, luxury watches
SUMMARY: More assets such as gold bars and watches have been seized by the authorities in Singapore, where a group of foreign nationals are being investigated in a money laundering scheme.

TITLE: Kenya to lead multinational force in Haiti to combat gangs
SUMMARY: The president of Kenya will deploy about 1,000 soldiers to lead a multinational force in Haiti, where the majority of its capital has been taken over by gangs.

TITLE: 4 dead, 5 injured in Romania following gas explosion, fire at highway construction site
SUMMARY: An explosion in Calimanesti, Romania, has caused four deaths and five injuries. The blast at a highway construction site may have bee caused by workers cracking a gas transport main.

TITLE: Italy's call for naval blockade may be only way to stem Europe's migrant crisis, expert says
SUMMARY: Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni is calling for an EU naval blockade to stem the continent's migrant crisis, something one expert believes is the only option.

TITLE: India tells citizens in Canada to 'exercise utmost caution' in dispute over murdered Sikh activist
SUMMARY: India’s foreign ministry is telling its citizens in Canada to “exercise utmost caution" in the latest escalation between the two countries after the killing of a Sikh activist.

TITLE: Bret Baier interviews Saudi Prince: Israel peace, 9/11 ties, Iran nuke fears: 'Cannot see another Hiroshima'
SUMMARY: Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman answered all questions put to him by Fox News' Bret Baier, including questions about Jamal Khashoggi's murder and ties to the 9/11 attacks.

TITLE: Dutch photographer Erwin Olaf, celebrated for diverse and stylized work, dead at 64
SUMMARY: Erwin Olaf, a Dutch photographer renowned for his distinctive and visually striking images of subjects ranging from LGBTQ+ nightlife to the Dutch royal family, has died. He was 64.

TITLE: UN General Assembly meets for second day as leaders discuss climate change, economy and Ukraine
SUMMARY: The United Nations General Assembly met for a second day Wednesday in New York City to speak about pressing issues facing the world

TITLE: Vietnamese energy think tank director arrested, marking sixth detention of climate expert in 2 years
SUMMARY: Vietnam authorities detained an energy think tank director on September 15, making it the sixth detention of a climate expert in the last two years, according to rights group.

TITLE: Iran has no regrets as anniversary of protester's death sparks mass arrests
SUMMARY: Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi blamed the U.S. and other Western countries for the unrest in his country last year, accusing the U.S. of attempting to destabilize Iran.

TITLE: Russia assailed by Albanian PM after failed attempt to prevent Ukraine President Zelenskyy from speaking at UN
SUMMARY: Albanian Prime Minister Edi Rama assailed Russia's failed attempt to prevent Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy from speaking at the United Nations Security Council on Wednesday.

TITLE: US citizen dies in northwestern Slovenia rafting accident, 2 others injured
SUMMARY: A United States citizen died and two others sustained minor injuries during a rafting incident in northwestern Slovenia, according to local authorities.

TITLE: London police officer charged with murder in fatal shooting of unarmed black man
SUMMARY: A police officer from Britain's London Metropolitan Police force has been indicted for murder over the fatal shooting of 24-year-old Chris Kaba.

TITLE: Protesters slam Biden's $6 billion deal with Iran, demand justice for victims killed by regime
SUMMARY: Protesters call out President Biden's $6 billion deal with Iran while demanding justice for the victims who were killed under Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi's regime.

TITLE: Bret Baier's week in Saudi Arabia yields behind-the-scenes look at country in transition: 'Tectonic changes'
SUMMARY: Saudi officials and local business owners spoke with Fox News Channel's chief political anchor about the changes in their country while addressing some notable controversies.

TITLE: Reporter names baby 'Methamphetamine Rules' but she has a work reason
SUMMARY: A journalist in Australia legally named her baby "Methamphetamine Rules" after testing if a government office would reject the name and offer a default option.

TITLE: Italy culls more than 30,000 pigs to counter spread of swine fever
SUMMARY: More than 30,000 pigs in Lombardy, a northern Italian region with the largest number of bred pigs in the country, has been culled to counter the spread of African swine fever.

TITLE: British tourist falls 300 feet to his death from Austria mountain ladder popular on Instagram: report
SUMMARY: A British tourist died after slipping off an aerial ladder and falling into a valley in the Dachstein Mountains in Austria, according to reports.

TITLE: Crews head to southwestern Greece to rescue nearly 90 migrants reportedly stuck on yacht
SUMMARY: About 90 migrants have been spotted on board a yacht in southwestern Greece 46 miles west of Pylos. Rescue operations were launched to rescue the migrants.

TITLE: 10 dead in eastern China after 2 tornadoes strike region within hours
SUMMARY: A dozen people were killed and four others became injured Tuesday after two tornadoes within hours made landfall in the Jiangsu province of eastern China.

TITLE: Monkey mayhem as wild animals wreak havoc in supermarket raid: video
SUMMARY: Thailand has faced a growing problem with its monkey population especially since the COVID lockdowns. Gangs of monkeys have been seen stealing food from stores, fighting among themselves and even causing harm to people.

TITLE: Mexico railway halts train operations after viral video showing migrants riding to the US
SUMMARY: Ferromex, Mexico's largest concessionary rail operator, said it would be stopping operations in the northern Mexico as migrants are climbing on freight cars seeking access to the U.S.

TITLE: Japanese crown prince visits Vietnam to mark 50th anniversary of diplomatic relations
SUMMARY: Crown Prince Akishino, of Japan, has arrived in Vietnam to celebrate their 50 years of friendship. Akishino will travel around Vietnam for five days.
